      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BACKCREEK BUTCH (1) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 450m at Grafton, taking a Grade 5 in a strong 25.32. Smart win two back and looks a key chance here. GIVE ME BUCKS (3) ran below best last time finishing sixth (25.98) over 457m at this track from Box 6. Goes very well from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Should be about the money. WARREGO RAIN (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (20.17) in a Grade 5 at Capalaba. Solid record here winning two races. One of the main contenders. CANYA ATOMIC (8) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
